The paper discusses theory related to probabilistic models and inference, which is a common theme in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of Poisson processes and slice sampling, which are commonly used in information theory and signal processing (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of hierarchical and dependent relations, which are commonly studied in social network analysis and data science (cs.SI, cs.DS).
